main event: Two lights were observed in the sky over Renton, Washington on March 26, 1957.
interesting points: The lights moved in a jagged flight path and changed direction and speed rapidly, suggesting intelligent control., The observation lasted for 2 minutes., The lights were first noticed at 13:57Z and could still be seen at 14:25Z., The sighting was later reported to the Washington State Patrol., The objects were speculated to be related to an airway beacon light located nearby.
